commit.message:
fix installing the localized manpage(s)

`Makefile`, ll. 92-94 :

Single quotes prevent the shell from substituting `$i`, hence why curr-
ently only the default manual page is being installed.

This patch fixes it by replacing them with double quotes.

commit.message:
Fix writeback settings not working

Size has to be set before setting uncompressible pages, but after setting the backing device, or it will error out.
Also change the filename "write" to "writeback", since no file called "write" exists.

commit.message:
fix bad `sed` statement

In some cases,     we need the `TEXTDOMAINDIR` variable to be different
from the installation directory of the locales: for example,  an ebuild
temporarily installs the files in "${D}" before installing them in  the
system: the locales should be installed in "${D}/usr/share/locales" but
`TEXTDOMAINDIR` should be equal to "/usr/share/locales".

Signed-off-by: Mattéo Rossillol‑‑Laruelle <beatussum@protonmail.com>
